unittitle.value: International Typographical Union Printed Ephemera Collection

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The International Typographical Union Printed Ephemera Collection is an artificial collection, collected and assembled by the staff of the Tamiment Library over the course of several decades. The files contain agreements, contracts and constitutions, as well as printed ephemera such as fliers, leaflets, newspaper clippings, pamphlets and other publications.

p.value:
Published citations should take the following form: 
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date; Collection name; Collection number; box number; folder number; 
                <lb/>Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives 
                <lb/>Elmer Holmes Bobst Library 
                <lb/>70 Washington Square South 
                <lb/>New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

The Library's Trade Union Printed Ephemera Files include material generated by federations and national, regional and local bodies, as well as departments and divisions of trade unions. While a small portion of the material is international in scope or associated with other regions of the United States, the majority of the collection relates to the New York metropolitan area.

The International Typographical Union Printed Ephemera Collection consists of constitutions, contracts, agreements, by-laws, memoranda, reports, and printed ephemera such as clippings, flyers, broadsides, leaflets, catalogs, press releases, programs, and pamphlets generated by the national, regional and local bodies, as well as departments and divisions of the union. The files are arranged alphabetically. Local 6 New York, NY is arranged as a separate series from the main union papers.
